        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 5:52PM CDT until June 8 at 6:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northwestern Potter County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 645 PM CDT.

* At 552 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 12 miles southwest
of Hartley, or 18 miles south of Dalhart, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Channing.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
